.TH dxprint 1X
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Ldxprint\*O \- Capture and print screen image.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*Ldxprint\*O [ \*Vflags\*O ] [ \*Vfile\*O ]
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "dxprint"
.iX "screen capture"
.iX "print Screen"
The dxprint (Print Screen) program allows you to capture the screen image
in printable form.
.PP
The available output formats are PostScript, Sixel, and DDIF (Digital Document
Interchange Format).
.PP
An optional time delay gives you time to rearrange the screen
to iconify or restack windows, or to give focus to the window
with the color map to be used for the capture.
.PP
Output is sent to the standard output unless \*Vfile\*O is supplied.
.PP
The \*L\-X\*O option displays the dxprint Graphical User Interface (GUI).
This reference page describes the dxprint command line interface. Use the
GUI help facility for help with the dxprint GUI.
.SH FLAGS
.PP
.SS Usage Diagrams
.if n .PP
.sS
\*Ldxprint \-X\*O
.sE
.sS
\*Ldxprint\*O [\*L\-p\*O] [\*L\-b|G\*O] [\*L\-f\*O] [\*L\-r\*O]
[\*Vgeom*\*O] [\*L\-t\*O \*Vseconds\*O] [\*L\-P \*Vqueue\*O] \\
.nL
               [\*L\-P \*Vqueue\*O] [\*Vfile\*O]
.sE
.sS
\*Ldxprint\*O [\*L\-p\*O] \*L\-c\*O [\*L\-f\*O] [\*Lgeom*\*O]
[\*L\-t\*O \*Vseconds\*O] [\*L\-P \*Vqueue\*O] [\*Vfile\*O]
.sE
.sS
\*Ldxprint\*O \*L\-D\*O [\*L\-b|G\*O] [\*L\-r\*O] [\*Vgeom*\*O]
[\*L\-t\*O \*Vseconds\*O] [\*L\-P \*Vqueue\*O] [\*Vfile\*O]
.sE
.sS
\*Ldxprint\*O \*L\-D\*O \*L\-c\*O [\*Vgeom*\*O] [\*L\-t\*O \*Vseconds\*O]
[\*L\-P \*Vqueue\*O] [\*Vfile\*O]
.sE
.sS
\*Ldxprint\*O \*L\-s\*O [\*L\-b|G\*O] [\*L\-a\*O] [\*L\-r\*O] [\*Vgeom*\*O]
[\*L\-t\*O \*Vseconds\*O] [\*L\-T\*O \*Vn\*O] \\
.nL
               [\*L\-P \*Vqueue\*O] [\*Vfile\*O]
.sE
.sS
\*Ldxprint\*O \*L\-s\*O \*L\-c\*O [\*Vgeom*\*O] [\*L\-t\*O \*Vseconds\*O]
[\*L\-T\*O \*Vn\*O] [\*L\-P \*Vqueue\*O] [\*Vfile\*O]
.sE
